India’s Bank Loans Rose 1.72 Trillion Rupees in Sept., RBI Says

-- B y   K a r t i k   G o y a l
-- 
2011-10-14T11:31:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-14/india-s-bank-loans-rose-1-72-trillion-rupees-in-sept-rbi-says.html
Indian banks’ loans rose by 1.72
trillion rupees ($35.1 billion) in September. The outstanding
advances stood at 42.2 trillion rupees, according to central
bank data.  Loans to industry and consumers rose 1.77 triillion rupees
during the period, while food credit declined 42.8 billion
rupees, the  Reserve Bank  of India said in an e-mailed statement
today. Deposits increased 1.99 trillion rupees in September.   Credit rose 21.4 percent, or by 7.44 trillion rupees, in
the 12 months through Sep. 30, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kartik Goyal in  New Delhi  at 
